<div class="a11y-page">
  <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>

  <h2>Our commitment</h2>
  <p>This site is committed to meeting <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/" rel="external">WCAG 2.2 Level AA</a> accessibility standards. I believe the web should work for everyone, and I hold my own work to the same standard I advocate for professionally.</p>

  <h2>Scope</h2>
  <p>This statement covers all pages on this site, including the homepage, case study pages, writing articles, and this accessibility statement.</p>

  <h2>Measures taken</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>All pages use semantic HTML5 with a logical heading hierarchy.</li>
    <li>All images include descriptive <code>alt</code> attributes.</li>
    <li>All interactive elements are keyboard navigable with visible focus indicators.</li>
    <li>Color contrast meets WCAG 2.2 Level AA minimums (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text and UI components).</li>
    <li>No information is conveyed by color alone.</li>
    <li>A skip navigation link is present on every page.</li>
    <li>External links are identified with <code>rel="external"</code> and communicated to users.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Known limitations</h2>
  <p>Placeholder images in the current version of this site do not yet have final descriptive alt text. These will be updated as real images are added.</p>

  <h2>Report an accessibility issue</h2>
  <p>If you encounter an accessibility barrier on this site, please contact me at <a href="mailto:contact@k80anderson.com">contact@k80anderson.com</a>. I take these reports seriously and will respond within five business days.</p>

  <h2>Last reviewed</h2>
  <p>This statement was last reviewed on <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>.</p>
</div>
